cs.IR, cs.WEB, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper analyzes the correlation between content and traffic of academic websites, which involves web search, information retrieval, web development, and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.WEB (Web Technologies), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
